## **4. SHADOWS & ELEVATION**

### 4.1 Shadow System (WPF-Optimized)

**Performance Note**: All shadows use maximum 24px blur for GPU compatibility.

| Level | Name | BlurRadius | ShadowDepth | Opacity | Color | Usage |
|-------|------|------------|-------------|---------|-------|-------|
| **0** | None | 0 | 0 | 0 | N/A | Sidebar, TopBar, flat elements |
| **1** | Subtle | 12px | 3px | 0.06 | #000000 | Hovered buttons, input focus |
| **2** | Standard | 20px | 6px | 0.10 | #000000 | Cards, stat tiles, list items |
| **3** | Floating | 24px | 10px | 0.16 | #000000 | Modals, dropdowns, toasts |

### 4.2 Shadow Enhancement on Hover

When element is hovered (cards, buttons):
- **Y-offset**: +6px (element lifts upward)
- **Blur increase**: +4px (maximum 28px total — acceptable for temporary state)
- **Opacity increase**: +0.04
- **Duration**: 220ms
- **X-offset**: 0px (shadow directly below, Apple-style)

### 4.3 WPF Implementation

```xml
<!-- Level 1: Subtle -->
<DropShadowEffect x:Key="Shadow1" 
                  BlurRadius="12" 
                  ShadowDepth="3" 
                  Opacity="0.06" 
                  Color="#000000"
                  Direction="270"/>

<!-- Level 2: Standard -->
<DropShadowEffect x:Key="Shadow2" 
                  BlurRadius="20" 
                  ShadowDepth="6" 
                  Opacity="0.10" 
                  Color="#000000"
                  Direction="270"/>

<!-- Level 3: Floating -->
<DropShadowEffect x:Key="Shadow3" 
                  BlurRadius="24" 
                  ShadowDepth="10" 
                  Opacity="0.16" 
                  Color="#000000"
                  Direction="270"/>
```

