## **8. DPI SCALING STRATEGY**

### 8.1 WPF DPI Awareness Configuration

**App Manifest** (app.manifest):
```xml
<application xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:asm.v3">
  <windowsSettings>
    <dpiAware xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/SMI/2005/WindowsSettings">true/PM</dpiAware>
    <dpiAwareness xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/SMI/2016/WindowsSettings">PerMonitorV2</dpiAwareness>
  </windowsSettings>
</application>
```

### 8.2 WPF Rendering Settings (Global)

**App.xaml.cs Application Startup**:
```csharp
// Enable per-monitor DPI awareness
if (Environment.OSVersion.Version.Major >= 6)
{
    SetProcessDpiAwareness(PROCESS_PER_MONITOR_DPI_AWARE);
}

// Apply to all windows
RenderOptions.ProcessRenderMode = RenderMode.Default; // Use GPU when available
```

**All XAML Elements**:
```xml
UseLayoutRounding="True"
SnapsToDevicePixels="True"
TextOptions.TextFormattingMode="Display"
TextOptions.TextRenderingMode="ClearType"
```

### 8.3 DPI Scaling Behavior

**Font Sizes**: All pt values scale automatically (96 DPI = 1×, 144 DPI = 1.5×, 192 DPI = 2×)

**Images & Icons**:
- Use vector (SVG via SvgImageSource) whenever possible
- For raster: Provide 1×, 1.5×, 2× versions
- Avatar images: Render at 2× resolution, display at 1×
- Empty state illustrations: SVG or 512px PNG (for 256dp display size)

**Shadows**: Automatically scale with DPI (20px blur @ 100% = 30px @ 150%)

**Testing Requirements**:
- Test at 100% (1920×1080)
- Test at 125% (common on 1080p laptops)
- Test at 150% (common on 1440p laptops)
- Test at 200% (4K monitors)

### 8.4 Layout Rounding

**Why UseLayoutRounding="True"**:
- Prevents blurry text on fractional pixels
- Ensures borders are exactly 1 device pixel
- Aligns all elements to physical pixel boundaries

**Apply to**:
- Window root
- All text containers
- All borders and separators
- All image containers

