## **47. PERFORMANCE TARGETS**

### 47.1 Timing Benchmarks

| Metric | Target | Measurement Point |
|--------|--------|-------------------|
| **Screen load** | <350ms | Navigation click → content visible |
| **Search response (online)** | <150ms | Keystroke → results appear |
| **Search response (cached)** | <50ms | Keystroke → results appear |
| **Animation frame rate** | 60 FPS | All animations, sustained |
| **Modal open** | <400ms | Click → fully visible |
| **Chart render** | <500ms | Data load → fully drawn |
| **List scroll** | 60 FPS | Smooth scrolling, no jank |
| **Button feedback** | <120ms | Click → visual response |

### 47.2 Resource Usage

| Resource | Limit | Notes |
|----------|-------|-------|
| **Memory (average)** | <500MB | During normal operation |
| **Memory (peak)** | <1GB | Under heavy load (1000+ members) |
| **CPU (average)** | <15% | Idle with live updates |
| **CPU (peak)** | <40% | During chart rendering |
| **Network (idle)** | <10KB/min | Background sync only |
| **Network (active)** | <1MB/min | Typical usage |
| **IndexedDB size** | <50MB | Cached data (typical) |

### 47.3 WPF-Specific Optimizations

**Rendering**:
- GPU acceleration: `RenderOptions.ProcessRenderMode = Default`
- Bitmap cache: Apply to sidebar, static cards
- Shadow blur: Maximum 24px
- Text: `UseLayoutRounding="True"`, `SnapsToDevicePixels="True"`

**Virtualization**:
- Lists >50 items: `VirtualizingStackPanel`
- `ScrollViewer.CanContentScroll="True"`
- Load in batches: 50-100 items

**Animations**:
- Use `RenderTransform` only (GPU-accelerated)
- Avoid animating: Width, Height, Margin
- Max simultaneous: 8 animations

