STEP 1.6: Update Business Logic Layer
1.6.1 Implement Facility-Aware Validation Rules
Member Registration Validation:
Existing Rule: Member must have unique card ID
New Rule: Card ID must be unique GLOBALLY (not just per facility)

Rationale: Members can access hammam/pool from multiple facilities
Validation: Check Members table WHERE CardID = @cardId (no facility filter)

New Rule: Member gender must match facility gender

If facility is Male-only → Member must be Male
If facility is Female-only → Member must be Female
If facility is Mixed (restaurant) → Any gender allowed
Implementation: Validation in CreateMemberAsync method

New Rule: Member can belong to multiple facilities (for hammam/pool)

Primary facility: Where membership was purchased
Allowed facilities: Calculated based on primary facility's shared access
Example: Gym member can access Hammam and Pool
Implementation: MemberFacilityAccess table (many-to-many)


Access Control Validation:
Existing Rule: Member must have active membership
Updated Rule: Member must have active membership + facility access rights
New Validation Logic:
ValidateAccess(cardId, facilityId):
  1. Find member by cardId
  2. Check membership is active (expiration date > today)
  3. Check member has access to target facility:
     a. If primary facility matches target → ALLOW
     b. If target is shared facility (hammam/pool) → Check time slot
     c. Otherwise → DENY
  4. If target is hammam/pool → Validate gender + time slot
     - Get current time slot for facility
     - Check member.Gender == timeSlot.Gender
     - If mismatch → DENY with reason "Currently reserved for [Gender]"
  5. If all checks pass → GRANT access, log event
Time Slot Validation:
IsTimeSlotValid(facilityId, memberGender, currentTime):
  1. Query TimeSlots WHERE FacilityID = @id AND DayOfWeek = @day
  2. Find slot where currentTime BETWEEN StartTime AND EndTime
  3. If no slot found → DENY (facility closed)
  4. If slot.Gender != memberGender → DENY (wrong gender)
  5. If slot.Gender == memberGender → ALLOW

Product Availability Validation:
New Rule: Product must be available in current facility

Global products (FacilityID = NULL) → Available everywhere
Facility-specific products → Only in assigned facility
Validation: GetAvailableProducts(facilityId) returns facility products + global

Example:

Protein powder (FacilityID = NULL) → Available in Gym and Salon
Barbell (FacilityID = 1, Gym) → Only in Gym
Hair dye (FacilityID = 2, Salon) → Only in Salon
Steak (FacilityID = 3, Restaurant) → Only in Restaurant


1.6.2 Implement Cross-Facility Business Rules
Shared Facility Access Rules:
Rule: Gym members (male) can access Hammam and Pool during male hours
Implementation:

When creating member at Gym → Automatically grant access to Hammam (4) and Pool (5)
Insert into MemberFacilityAccess table: (MemberId, FacilityId=4), (MemberId, FacilityId=5)

Rule: Salon clients (female) can access Hammam and Pool during female hours
Implementation: Same as above, but for female members
Rule: Restaurant has no members (walk-in customers only)
Implementation:

Do NOT show "Members" screen on Restaurant PC
Orders are associated with table numbers, not member IDs
No membership validation for restaurant access


Staff Multi-Facility Assignment:
Rule: Staff can work at multiple facilities with different roles
