Performance Optimization:

Use compiled queries for frequent date-based queries
Index on (FacilityID, ScheduledDate, Status)
Paginate results for date range queries (>100 appointments)


**Query Example (HasConflictAsync):**
Logic:
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Appointments
WHERE StaffID = @staffId
AND ScheduledDate = @date
AND Status IN (1, 2, 3) -- SCHEDULED, CONFIRMED, IN_PROGRESS
AND (@excludeId IS NULL OR AppointmentID != @excludeId)
AND (
-- New appointment starts during existing appointment
(@newStart >= ScheduledTime AND @newStart < DATEADD(MINUTE, Duration, ScheduledTime))
OR
-- New appointment ends during existing appointment
(@newEnd > ScheduledTime AND @newEnd <= DATEADD(MINUTE, Duration, ScheduledTime))
OR
-- New appointment fully contains existing appointment
(@newStart <= ScheduledTime AND @newEnd >= DATEADD(MINUTE, Duration, ScheduledTime))
)
If COUNT > 0 → CONFLICT EXISTS

